<doc id="1221702" wikidata="Q7609296" url="?curid=1221702" title="Stephen Garvin">
<text>Stephen Garvin (c. 1826 – 23 November 1874), born in Cashel, County Tipperary, was an Irish recipient of the Victoria Cross, the highest award for gallantry in the face of the enemy that can be awarded to British and Commonwealth forces.

==Details==
He was around 31 years old, and a colour-sergeant in the 1st Battalion, 60th Rifles, British Army during the Indian Mutiny when the following deed took place on 23 June 1857 at Delhi, India for which he was awarded the Victoria Cross:
==Further information==

=== Death ===
Garvin died in Chesterton, Cambridge on 23 November 1874, and is buried in St. Andrew&#x27;s Parish Churchyard there. 

=== Victoria Cross auctioning ===
His Victoria Cross is in private ownership, having been bought by Conservative peer Lord Ashcroft at auction in 2014.

